 <section class="hero"><h1>Load Order</h1><p class="lead">This page covers LOOT as a helper, DML plugin sorting, and starter text files for a Pocket Mojave setup.</p></section><section><h2>Use LOOT as a check, not a magic button</h2><p><a href="https://loot.github.io/">LOOT</a> supports Fallout: New Vegas and can identify missing masters, warnings, dirty plugins, and order suggestions. Use it on PC when you can, then copy the result back into DML/GameNative.</p><ol><li>Install LOOT on a Windows PC or a Windows environment that can see your New Vegas folder.</li><li>Make sure the same plugins are present as the DML profile you are checking.</li><li>Run LOOT for Fallout: New Vegas.</li><li>Read the warnings before sorting.</li><li>Apply sorting only if the warnings make sense.</li><li>Compare LOOT's result against this guide's order shape.</li><li>Use DML to match the order on Android.</li></ol></section>[m
[31m-<section><h2>Sorting plugins in Droid Mod Loader</h2><ol><li>Open DML.</li><li>Select the Pocket Mojave profile.</li><li>Deploy Current State.</li><li>Run plugin discovery.</li><li>Enable the guide plugins you installed.</li><li>Move official DLC to the top, then YUP, then other fixes, then UI, gameplay, and visual plugins.</li><li>Export plugin outputs.</li><li>Launch the game from GameNative and check that the expected plugins are active.</li></ol><aside class="callout"><strong>Important</strong><div>Plugin order controls ESM/ESP loading. Mod priority controls loose file conflicts. They are not the same list.</div></aside></section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<div class="callout warning"><h3>Plugin order and mod priority are not the same thing</h3><p>Plugin order controls ESM and ESP loading. Mod priority controls loose file conflicts. DML has to handle both, but they are different lists.</p></div>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section><h2>Sorting plugins in Droid Mod Loader</h2><ol><li>Open DML.</li><li>Select the Pocket Mojave profile.</li><li>Deploy Current State.</li><li>Use DML's plugin list/load order view to confirm the enabled ESM and ESP files match this page.</li><li>Enable the guide plugins you installed.</li><li>Move official DLC to the top, then YUP, then other fixes, then UI, gameplay, and visual plugins.</li><li>Export plugin outputs.</li><li>Launch the game from GameNative and check that the expected plugins are active.</li></ol></section>[m
